# Interaction States üëÜ

- `:hover`: styling when the mouse is over the element.
- `:active`: styling when the element is being clicked.
- `:focus`: styling when the element has input focus (clicked or tabbed to).

```css
button:hover {
  background-color: blue;
  color: white;
}

input:focus {
  border: 2px solid blue;
  outline: none;
}
```

# Structural Selectors üèóÔ∏è

Select elements based on their position in the document tree.

- `:first-child`: Selects specific element that is the first child of its parent.
- `:last-child`: Selects the last child.
- `:nth-child(n)`: Selects the nth child (e.g., `2`, `odd`, `even`).

```css
/* Stripe Effect */
tr:nth-child(even) {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
}
```

# ::before & ::after ü™Ñ

These are powerful! You can inject content purely with CSS.

You MUST specify the `content` property.

```css
h1::before {
  content: "ü¶Ñ ";
}

.price::after {
  content: " USD";
  color: gray;
  font-size: 0.8em;
}
```

# Creative Shapes üé®

They are often used for visual effects without adding HTML markup (shapes, tooltips, underlines).

```css
/* Animated Underline */
a::after {
  content: '';
  display: block;
  width: 0;
  height: 2px;
  background: blue;
  transition: width .3s;
}
a:hover::after {
  width: 100%;
}
```

# ::selection üñçÔ∏è

Matches the portion of an element that is selected by a user (drag-highlighted).

```css
::selection {
  color: red;
  background: yellow;
}
```
Note: You can only apply a few properties (color, background, cursor, outline).

# :not() üôÖ

Selects every element that is NOT the specified element/selector.

```css
/* Style all inputs EXCEPT submit buttons */
input:not([type="submit"]) {
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
}
```

